00:23:56.110 --> 00:23:57.840
has focus.

00:23:57.840 --> 00:23:59.940
It follows the same
styles as the hover,

00:23:59.940 --> 00:24:02.720
and it also has the outline,
the browser's default caret

00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:06.560
to show me, yup, that's
where I am right now.

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.790
Turn off images.

00:24:08.790 --> 00:24:11.557
Images aren't necessarily always
going to load anyway, but just

00:24:11.557 --> 00:24:12.140
turn them off.

00:24:12.140 --> 00:24:13.410
Let's see what happens.

00:24:13.410 --> 00:24:15.170
Remember users can
have bad connections.

00:24:15.170 --> 00:24:17.184
The images can be messed up.

00:24:17.184 --> 00:24:18.850
If you can still make
sense of the page,

00:24:18.850 --> 00:24:19.891
you're doing pretty well.

00:24:19.891 --> 00:24:22.850
If content is missing,
you've got a problem.

00:24:22.850 --> 00:24:24.950
If you can't use
the site at all,

00:24:24.950 --> 00:24:26.620
you've got an even
bigger problem.

00:24:26.620 --> 00:24:29.130
It also lets you see if the
alternative text you've put

00:24:29.130 --> 00:24:31.430
behind those images is useful.

00:24:31.430 --> 00:24:33.390
So here's the same page.

00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:35.000
I turn off the images.

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:37.340
The page is still usable.

00:24:37.340 --> 00:24:40.370
Some things to note-- up in
the corner, upper left corner

00:24:40.370 --> 00:24:43.501
where the logo was, it
