These project a
little differently

00:28:38.570 --> 00:28:40.170
than they appear onscreen.

00:28:40.170 --> 00:28:42.320
But onscreen, it's still usable.

00:28:42.320 --> 00:28:43.420
It's still legible.

00:28:43.420 --> 00:28:44.716
The colors still make sense.

00:28:44.716 --> 00:28:45.840
You're not losing anything.

00:28:48.460 --> 00:28:50.290
Look for captions
and transcripts.

00:28:50.290 --> 00:28:53.490
If you have videos, if
you have audio files,

00:28:53.490 --> 00:28:56.050
check to see if there
are audio descriptions.

00:28:56.050 --> 00:28:58.630
Look to see if there are
links to those transcripts

00:28:58.630 --> 00:28:59.880
and those captions.

00:28:59.880 --> 00:29:01.300
You want them to
be easy to find.

00:29:01.300 --> 00:29:03.550
You still build them into
whatever the player is,

00:29:03.550 --> 00:29:05.612
but in case that player
doesn't support it

00:29:05.612 --> 00:29:07.070
or the assistive
technology doesn't

00:29:07.070 --> 00:29:09.250
support the player's
way of supporting it,

00:29:09.250 --> 00:29:10.720
keep plain text links.

00:29:10.720 --> 00:29:12.180
It's great.

00:29:12.180 --> 00:29:13.930
Text alternatives
are a good way to go.

